                    <span>CGI character rigging is tough stuff. Those of us who have to<BR>sit in some studio dealing with this stuff every day know that<BR>it can take years to really get fluid at this art form.<BR> <BR> I thought "Stop Staring" used an intuitive, user friendly<BR>and fun approach to teaching this difficult subject.<BR> <BR> Not only is the technical side simply explained but the author<BR>does a great job of teaching how to artistically create voice <BR>sync animation.....using our own CGI characters or those <BR>provided on a disk....to create fantastically good CGI animations.<BR> I know It'll be helpful to my career.<P> Nice Job to all involved on "Stop Staring".</span>
                  
              
